Have a look at the package `redux-persist`. This contains a function `persistStore` and the `PersistGate` component. This will rehydrate the store after reloading the page. And you have to choose in wich browser store the data will be saved. You can decide between session storage (per tab) or locale storage (per domain)

Here is the example for session storage

```
import { PersistGate } from &#39;redux-persist/lib/integration/react&#39;
import { persistStore } from &#39;redux-persist&#39;
import { persistReducer } from &#39;redux-persist&#39;
import storage from &#39;redux-persist/es/storage/session&#39;

const persistConfig = {
    key: &#39;root&#39;,
    storage,
}

const persistedReducer = persistReducer(persistConfig, reducer)

const store = createStore(persistedReducer);
const persistor = persistStore(store)
const customHistory = createHashHistory();



ReactDOM.render(
  &lt;Provider store = {store}&gt;
        &lt;PersistGate persistor={persistor}&gt;
...
```

